'''HMCS ''Resolute''''' ([[Hull classification symbol (Canada)|hull number]] MCB 154) was a {{sclass2-|Bay|minesweeper}} that was constructed for the [[Royal Canadian Navy]] during the [[Cold War]]. Entering service in 1954, the ship served on the [[British Columbia Coast|West Coast of Canada]] until 1964 when ''Resolute'' was [[Ship decommissioning|decommissioned]]. The vessel was discarded in 1965.

==Design and description==
The Bay class were designed and ordered as replacements for the [[Second World War]]-era minesweepers that the Royal Canadian Navy operated at the time. Similar to the {{sclass2-|Ton|minesweeper|1}}, they were constructed of wood planking and aluminum framing.<ref name=m1>Macpherson and Barrie, p. 271</ref><ref name=con1>Gardiner and Chumbley, p. 49</ref>

[[Displacement (ship)|Displacing]] {{convert|390|LT|t}} standard at {{convert|412|LT|t}} at deep load, the minesweepers were {{convert|152|ft|m|abbr=on}} [[Length overall|long]] with a [[Beam (nautical)|beam]] of {{convert|28|ft|m|abbr=on}} and a [[Draft (hull)|draught]] of {{convert|8|ft|m|abbr=on}}.<ref name=m1/><ref name=con1/> They had a complement of 38 officers and ratings.<ref name=m1/><ref group=note>Gardiner and Chumbley claim the complement was 40.</ref>

The Bay-class minesweepers were powered by two [[General Motors|GM]] 12-cylinder [[diesel engine]]s driving two shafts creating {{convert|2400|bhp|lk=in}}. This gave the ships a maximum speed of {{convert|16|kn|lk=in}} and a range of {{convert|3290|nmi|lk=in}} at {{convert|12|kn}}.<ref name=con1/><ref name=j1>Moore, p. 82</ref> The ships were armed with one [[40 mm Bofors]] gun and were equipped with minesweeping gear.<ref name=m1/><ref name=con1/>

==Operational history==
The ship's [[keel]] was laid down on 29 August 1951 by [[Kingston Shipbuilding]] at their yard in  [[Kingston, Ontario|Kingston]], [[Ontario]]. Named for a [[Resolute Bay|bay]] located in [[Nunavut]], ''Resolute'' was [[Ship naming and launching|launched]] on 20 June 1953. The ship was [[Ship commissioning|commissioned]] on 16 September 1954.<ref name=mac276>Macpherson and Barrie, p. 276</ref>

Upon commissioning, ''Resolute'' joined the [[First Canadian Minesweeping Squadron]].<ref>{{cite magazine |title=New 'Sweeper Commissioned |magazine=The Crowsnest |location=Ottawa |publisher=Queen's Printer |date=October 1954 |volume=6 |number=12 |pages=3}}</ref> In May 1956, the First Canadian Minesweeping Squadron deployed as part of the NATO minesweeping exercise Minex Sweep Clear One in the western Atlantic.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=First Canadian Minesweeper Squadron |magazine=The Crowsnest |publisher=Queen's Printer |location=Ottawa |date=August 1956 |volume=8 |number=10 |pages=18}}</ref> The ship [[Ship decommissioning|paid off]] on 14 February 1964.<ref name=mac276/> In 1965, ''Resolute'' was declared surplus.<ref name=mac276/><ref>Colledge, p. 528</ref>

